paragraph.content:
“PCA Meeting” shall mean any meeting, including hearings in the context of PCA
                Proceedings and conferences, convened by the
                PCA;

item.content:
(b) inviolability for all papers and documents for the purpose of their
                communications with the PCA and in relation to PCA Proceedings or PCA
                Meetings;

(c) for purposes of their communications in relation to PCA Proceedings or PCA
                Meetings, the right to receive and send papers and documents in whatever form by
                duly identified couriers or in sealed bags;

(d) exemption from immigration restrictions or alien registration when they
                travel for purposes of their participation in PCA Proceedings or PCA Meetings;
